1️⃣ git init

👉 Meaning:
Creates a new Git repository in your project

👉 Simple:
“Start tracking this folder using Git”
2️⃣ git add .

👉 Meaning:
Adds all files to staging area

👉 Simple:
“Prepare all files to be saved”

3️⃣ git commit -m "message"

👉 Meaning:
Saves changes permanently with a message

👉 Simple:
“Take a snapshot of project”

4️⃣ git branch -M main

👉 Meaning:
Renames branch to main

👉 Simple:
“Set main branch as default”

5️⃣ git remote add origin <repo-link>

👉 Meaning:
Connects your local project to GitHub repository

👉 Simple:
“Link my project to GitHub”

6️⃣ git push -u origin main

👉 Meaning:
Uploads code to GitHub

👉 Simple:
“Send my code to GitHub”

7️⃣ git push

👉 Meaning:
Push latest changes

👉 Simple:
“Update code on GitHub”

8️⃣ git pull

👉 Meaning:
Downloads latest changes from GitHub

👉 Simple:
“Get updated code from GitHub”

9️⃣ git clone <repo-link>

👉 Meaning:
Copies repository to your system

👉 Simple:
“Download project from GitHub”
